9
-I got you. ]

31:31.800 --> 31:32.960
[Teresa sighs]

31:36.590 --> 31:37.579
[knock on window]

31:37.630 --> 31:38.847
-Oh!
-Yes!

31:39.460 --> 31:40.495
[Cade clears throat]

31:41.940 --> 31:42.929
-Hey-hey.
-Hey!

31:42.980 --> 31:44.322
-What's up, buddy?
-Hey.

31:45.070 --> 31:46.116
I'll take that.

31:49.950 --> 31:51.941
So, uh, how'd it go?

31:51.990 --> 31:53.207
The kids had a great time.

31:53.250 --> 31:55.514
-And Camilla, too?
-Camilla, too.

31:56.470 --> 31:57.607
[indistinct]

31:58.130 --> 31:59.256
It's great to hear.

31:59.300 --> 32:00.949
Carmen said to thank you again.

32:01.000 --> 32:02.251
It really meant
the world to her

32:02.310 --> 32:04.119
to get to spend time
with her grandkids.

32:04.180 --> 32:05.477
That's great. Thank you.

32:05.530 --> 32:06.918
Just doing my job.

32:06.960 --> 32:08.780
Speaking of which,
I'm late for an interview.

32:08.830 --> 32:10.229
Call you tomorrow
with the full download?

32:10.270 --> 32:11.259
Yeah, sounds good.

32:11.320 --> 32:12.833
All right. Bye, kids.

32:12.880 --> 32:13.926
-Bye.
-Bye.

32:15.100 --> 32:16.146
So?

32:16.190 --> 32:17.748
CADE: SO...

32:17.800 --> 32:18.971
you had fun?

32:19.020 --> 32:20.408
ROBERTO:
Yeah, it was great.

32:20.460 --> 32:22.621
We watched Disney Plus
and she made chilaquiles.

32:22.670 --> 32:24.490
-Aw.
-[|aughs] I love chilaquiles.

32:24.550 --> 32:25.756
Hey, Camilla, uh,
where's your elephant?

32:25.810 --> 32:26.799
Did you forget Snuffy?

32:26.850 --> 32:27.976
CAMILLA:
Snuffy's at Grandma's.

32:28.030 --> 32:29.247
He's gonna live there

32:29.290 --> 32:30.803
so I'll get to play
with him next week.

32:30.860 --> 32:32.111
Next week?

32:32.160 --> 32:33.684
Grandma said we're gonna
see her all the time.

32:33.730 --> 32:34.810
Is that cool?

32:37.040 --> 32:38.120
TERESA: Uh...

32:41.910 --> 32:43.958
[soft music playing]

32:50.350 --> 32:51.487
What happens now?

32:52.840 --> 32:55.058
Well, the detectives
will ask you some questions

32:55.660 --> 32:56.831
but I'll be there with you.

32:57.190 --> 32:58.669
Am I going to jail?

32:59.490 --> 33:01.799
MINNICK: Tony was a bad man
and that money was tainted.

33:01.840 --> 33:03.319
You don't need to worry
about going to jail.

33:04.190 --> 33:06.146
-What you need to worry about--
-You don't need to tell me.

33:06.590 --> 33:07.716
Tell you what?

33:08.420 --> 33:11.025
I need to start
earning back my integrity.

33:11.720 --> 33:13.028
I know I do.

33:13.070 --> 33:14.150
[chuckles]

33:14.680 --> 33:15.988
Is that what I was gonna say?

33:16.510 --> 33:18.853
"Real integrity
is doing the right thing,

33:18.900 --> 33:20.640
"knowing that
nobody's gonna know

33:20.690 --> 33:22.169
-whether you did it or not."
-"...did it or not."

33:23.560 --> 33:25.118
And what's that?

33:25.170 --> 33:27.695
It's that Oprah quote
you used to start class with.

33:27.740 --> 33:29.048
Look at you

33:29.090 --> 33:30.910
remembering every word.

33:31.530 --> 33:33.782
I remember everything
you told us.

33:34.270 --> 33:37.000
I didn't know what integrity
was before I met you.

33:41.100 --> 33:42.271
I'm gonna do better.

33:43.410 --> 33:44.445
Starting right now.

33:46.630 --> 33:48.018
And I'm gonna help you.

34:00.210 --> 34:01.893
[horse nickers]

34:04.080 --> 34:05.297
BILL:
It's been too long.

34:08.390 --> 34:10.426
I'm sorry, Mags, I really am.

34:12.220 --> 34:14.302
I should've handled that
differently with Wyatt.

34:15.090 --> 34:16.398
I got protective

34:17.570 --> 34:19.128
instead of being trusting

34:19.920 --> 34:21.444
of you and your decisions.

34:23.010 --> 34:24.056
Thanks, Dad.

34:24.670 --> 34:25.739
[sighs deeply]

34:26.450 --> 34:27.929
I've been thinking about it...

34:28.450 --> 34:30.179
and I can't imagine
what it must be like

34:30.240 --> 34:31.719
watching a child grow up.

34:31.760 --> 34:32.931
Hard.

34:34.370 --> 34:35.587
[sighs] There are days
I wish I could slow it down.

34:35.630 --> 34:36.972
But I can't.

34:38.770 --> 34:39.805
I'm getting older.

34:40.770 --> 34:42.112
I'm almost 15.

34:42.680 --> 34:44.466
I need to be able
to have boys in my life

34:44.510 --> 34:46.637
who aren't completely
afraid of you.

34:46.690 --> 34:48.988
A little afraid of me
is okay though, right?

34:50.610 --> 34:52.032
Wouldn't have it
any other way.

34:54.960 --> 34:57.690
I do need you to give Wyatt
another chance though.

34:59.270 --> 35:00.214
For me.

35:00.270 --> 35:01.658
Whoa.

35:02.310 --> 35:04.005
I'd do anything for you, honey.

35:04.050 --> 35:05.312
'Course I will.

35:07.270 --> 35:09.090
You're just growing up so fast.

35:09.670 --> 35:11.228
I get scared.

35:11.280 --> 35:12.315
Sorry.

35:20.550 --> 35:22.279
Yo. You been here all night?

35:22.330 --> 35:24.286
I came in early.
I wanted to clear the inbox.

35:24.330 --> 35:26.469
Yeah, I get diving into work
after a breakup.

35:26.510 --> 35:28.114
But you're taking time
for yourself though, right?

35:28.160 --> 35:29.593
Trying to at least.

35:29.640 --> 35:31.949
If you ever wanna get
in the water, give me a shout.

35:31.990 --> 35:33.514
I'll take you for a surf.

35:33.560 --> 35:35.039
There's no better way
for clearing your head.

35:35.080 --> 35:36.297
Thanks, Cade.

35:36.350 --> 35:38.306
Yeah, I, uh, I might
take you up on that.

35:42.000 --> 35:43.046
[door opens]

35:44.310 --> 35:45.356
You wanted to see me?

35:46.310 --> 35:47.390
Yeah, sit.

35:49.010 --> 35:50.830
I sent some deputies over to

35:51.710 --> 35:53.758
pick up Isobel's
former foster mother.

35:55.930 --> 35:59.752
Think it's safe to say
she's not part of
the system anymore.

36:00.940 --> 36:02.157
Well, that's good to hear.

36:02.760 --> 36:04.500
How many years
were you a teacher?

36:05.030 --> 36:07.157
Six. Why?

36:07.200 --> 36:09.760
Wanted to know how long
it takes for someone to know.

36:10.950 --> 36:12.201
To know what?

36:12.250 --> 36:13.899
To know exactly
what a kid needs.

36:15.040 --> 36:16.996
What to say or do,

36:17.040 --> 36:18.348
how hard to push.

36:19.780 --> 36:20.826
It's a gift.

36:20.870 --> 36:22.303
I don't know about a gift.

36:22.350 --> 36:23.829
I was just doing my job.

36:23.870 --> 36:25.861
I don't think you've ever
just done anything.

36:26.920 --> 36:28.694
That's why I wanted to see you.

36:29.440 --> 36:31.226
I've been going through
this mountain

36:31.270 --> 36:34.137
of Sheriff Bradford's
unfinished paperwork...

36:34.970 --> 36:36.881
and it seems you're due
for a promotion.

36:36.930 --> 36:38.227
Yeah, well, I don't think
Sheriff Bradford--

36:38.280 --> 36:41.010
Which isn't why
I'm offering one to you.

36:41.060 --> 36:42.368
In my short time here,

36:43.410 --> 36:45.196
I've seen more than enough.

36:45.240 --> 36:48.061
Selflessness and initiative...

36:49.070 --> 36:51.197
that some don't manage
their entire career.

36:53.290 --> 36:54.848
So that's why I'd like
to offer you--

36:54.900 --> 36:55.855
MINNICK: Sir.

36:55.900 --> 36:57.208
I'm sorry.

36:57.250 --> 36:59.810
_ Idon't mean
to interrupt you, um...

37:00.780 --> 37:02.122
but I gotta be honest with you,

37:02.170 --> 37:03.899
I don't wanna know
what the promotion is.

37:03.960 --> 37:06.520
-Y_ou don't?
-I appreCIate it, of course.

37:06.570 --> 37:07.958
More than you know.

37:08.960 --> 37:11.428
But no matter what it is,
I'm gonna turn it down,

37:11.490 --> 37:13.742
so, the way I'm thinking,

37:13.790 --> 37:15.269
it's better not to know.

37:15.320 --> 37:16.924
And why would you turn it down?

37:17.490 --> 37:19.310
Because I wanna finish
what I started.

37:20.620 --> 37:21.666
And what's that?

37:22.500 --> 37:23.569
MINNICK:
Training Joseph.

37:24.800 --> 37:26.324
He's gonna be a great deputy.

37:26.980 --> 37:28.322
But the work
isn't finished yet.

37:29.200 --> 37:30.280
Like I said...

37:30.940 --> 37:32.498
you've never just done anything.

37:34.290 --> 37:36.110
Promotion's here
when you're ready.

37:37.210 --> 37:38.245
Thank you, sir.

37:41.300 --> 37:42.688
I owe you a second thank you.

37:43.870 --> 37:46.259
-For what?
-MINNICK:
For believing in me,

37:46.300 --> 37:48.086
for helping out with Isobel

37:48.130 --> 37:50.439
with no questions
and no conditions.

37:50.960 --> 37:52.780
That's all this is really about.

37:54.310 --> 37:55.356
The big wins...

37:57.230 --> 37:59.004
the unimaginable losses.

38:01.140 --> 38:02.744
We're here to help each other.

38:02.800 --> 38:06.622
Otherwise... _
we're just passm' time.

38:29.350 --> 38:30.954
Deputy Minnick.
There you are.

38:31.000 --> 38:32.695
I've got a new assignment
for you.

38:33.390 --> 38:34.732
This district attorney...

38:38.490 --> 38:39.787
You're not coming?

38:39.830 --> 38:41.001
MINNICK: I'm not.

38:41.490 --> 38:44.004
No. But thank you
for the invite.

38:44.060 --> 38:45.573
And the opportunity.
I appreciate it.

38:46.360 --> 38:48.009
Are you sure you know
what you're doing?

38:49.370 --> 38:50.314
I think so.

38:51.720 --> 38:54.325
This isn't just an invite
to an open bar event.

38:55.370 --> 38:57.235
This is my way of saying
you'll have a place

38:57.290 --> 38:58.234
in my command structure.

38:58.290 --> 38:59.678
If you're elected.

39:05.900 --> 39:07.037
WhenI'm elected.

39:09.040 --> 39:10.860
I really appreciate
everything you've done for me

39:11.690 --> 39:13.646
and for the confidence
you have in me.

39:13.690 --> 39:15.385
But I've been doing
some soul searching

39:15.440 --> 39:16.862
and the thing I've come up with

39:16.910 --> 39:19.083
is that what I really wanna do,

39:19.610 --> 39:21.009
what I am going to do,

39:21.050 --> 39:22.358
is my job.

39:23.400 --> 39:25.482
And right now,
my job is to start a shift

39:25.530 --> 39:27.873
with a young deputy
that's in need of my guidance.

39:29.060 --> 39:31.358
I can't argue with you
wanting to do your job.

39:31.890 --> 39:32.925
I respect that.

39:35.930 --> 39:37.272
But I'm not gonna lie to you.

39:38.110 --> 39:40.283
You're making
a very big mistake.

39:41.640 --> 39:45.246
District Attorney Riley
is running for sheriff now, too.

39:45.730 --> 39:47.675
She and Bill, regardless of
whether he's running or not

39:47.730 --> 39:49.027
will tear each other apart.

39:49.080 --> 39:50.559
And when the dust settles...

39:52.430 --> 39:54.079
I'll be the last man standing.

39:55.300 --> 39:57.086
At that point, you can
either stand beside me...

39:57.610 --> 39:58.645
or in my way.

40:00.740 --> 40:01.786
Yes, sir.

40:05.960 --> 40:08.702
[sighs]

40:08.750 --> 40:10.570
WOMAN [on phone]:
Mark Greenburg
from theLA Times

40:10.620 --> 40:12.406
-returning your call.
-Great. Thanks.

40:14.280 --> 40:16.407
Mark. Sheriff Hollister.

40:16.450 --> 40:19.055
I wanted to talk to you
about that LAPD detective

40:19.110 --> 40:20.759
the Sheriff's Department
arrested.

40:22.760 --> 40:25.149
Yeah, Detective Johnson,
that's him.

40:27.160 --> 40:29.674
Word on the street is
the DA's lookin' to cut a deal.

40:31.470 --> 40:33.290
How'd you like to hear
my side of the story?

40:35.210 --> 40:37.462
Volleyball tournament
in Venice tomorrow.

40:37.950 --> 40:40.418
-You are coming.
-Venice is my spot

40:40.480 --> 40:42.903
but volleyball is--
it's not my game.

40:42.960 --> 40:45.656
You're gonna miss out on
a lot of thirsty badge bunnies.

40:45.700 --> 40:47.600
Work comes first,
you know why?

40:48.180 --> 40:49.829
'Cause they're
the ones who pay.

40:49.880 --> 40:53.395
Exactly. So I will catch you
and your badge bunnies later.

40:54.530 --> 40:56.088
Are you sure this is
about work and not,

40:56.140 --> 40:57.619
I don't know, about Minnick?

40:58.230 --> 40:59.572
I get the feeling, like,

40:59.630 --> 41:01.621
there's something
going on between you two.

41:01.670 --> 41:02.750
JOSEPH: Yeah, well,
feelings are not facts.

41:02.800 --> 41:04.973
And there's definitely nothing.

41:05.810 --> 41:06.936
Carter.

41:06.980 --> 41:08.971
-Hi.
-Go home.

41:09.030 --> 41:10.065
Okay.

41:12.990 --> 41:15.379
-What?
-Watch out for that one.

41:15.860 --> 41:17.589
-I hear you.
-I don't want you to hear me.

41:17.640 --> 41:18.982
I want you to listen.

41:20.260 --> 41:21.420
Let's go.

41:30.270 --> 41:31.339
Hold on.

41:32.270 --> 41:33.305
What's up?

41:33.360 --> 41:34.520
Break down your shotgun.

41:36.660 --> 41:37.615
Really?

41:37.660 --> 41:39.218
Did I stutter?

41:40.410 --> 41:41.479
All right. Gotcha.

42:02.210 --> 42:03.859
Operable and patrol ready.

42:03.910 --> 42:04.945
All right.

42:05.780 --> 42:06.860
Do it again.

42:15.220 --> 42:17.393
Keep your eyes
on the street, Deputy.

43:02.620 --> 43:04.576
Captioned by Point.360
